race.comment: A few promising types come together in an interesting race. CRIMSON WINGS (7) took a sit behind the speed then worked home well to get up for second last start over 1200m at Gosford. Nicely placed over an extra 100m on a bigger track today. Looks the testing material. FIRE 'N' STONE (11) was facing the starter for only the second time when she saluted comfortably over today's trip at Canberra at her latest appearance. Needs a bit of luck from a sticky gate but if it comes she is a major contender. CAPTIVATING TYCOON (2) continued the promising start to his career when beaten narrowly over 1200m at Gosford recently. Found the line well on that occasion so an extra 100m with a longer run home looks ideal. CUBAN CIGAR (8) came with a huge finish but just ran out of ground at the Beaumont track last start. Very fit now and will enjoy this slightly longer trip. DIVA LAS VEGAS (5) is fitter for two runs back from a 20-month lay-off and might be ready to show something.
